data.title: Good Mexican Food
data.text:
We have been here many times.  It is a busy place, but service is good and can keep up. We will go out with friends for dinner or lunch - good Mexican food - good prices. This is not a high class place, but good place to stop for some quick eats after work. We go here when we get tired of fast food and want some home cooked Mexican. Good Salsa and Chips - everything good.  Get the Chicken Quesadilla it's great.
We live here. We know.

data.title: Local Place & Great Food!
data.text: Chevo's has the BEST refried beans I've ever had--especially in their bean and cheese burritos!  Love the grilled shrimp tacos and the chile rellenos.  It is a louder place at times, but a great local hangout.  Sometimes getting your food takes some time, but they keep your table stocked with warm chips and fresh salsa!  They do have regular daily specials.  Oh, and you can call in for take out, too!

data.title: nice little stop
data.text: Good food good service been going here for many years ...people are friendly and so are the customers ..we always have a good time when we stop in here..

data.title: Great visits most of the time
data.text: Nice place..people friendly..especially busy Friday nights.. careful...good fresh food, owner always present..sangria on ice w salted rim DELICIOUS... super good steak Picado.. most of the time great service..tacos fresh and good! Menudo awesome on the weekends..shrimp ceviche tostadas fresh and not fishy...don't try the fajitas, didn't stand out for me... torta de asada is good, catnitas are good too.

data.title: lovebugs5
data.text: YUMMY!!!! This little Mexican setting is awesome!!!! The best chili verde burritos! The people who run this place are very friendly. Very busy little place!

data.title: ** Mexican food
data.text: Love the food and salsa and chips.  The best beans in the Victor Valley.  Easy in and out for the take out.

data.title: Love this place!
data.text: It's great, real mexican food!  The refried beans and the bean & cheese burritos are the best!!!  Love the chile rellenos and shrimp tacos, too!  Great atmosphere!

data.title: Great food, Great price
data.text: we always enjoy eating at Chevos.  The food is always good. you cant go wrong.  it is one of our best Mexican restaurants in the high desert. Chips and salsa are always hot. The staff always greet you when you come in and you are seated quickly.  It can get busy and sometimes the wait may be a bit long. But the food is always worth the wait. They have specials everyday. and prices are great.

data.title: Good fish tacos!
data.text:
Casual and friendly. 
. Kind of out of the way and surprising. I thought it was a fast food place but its a full on restaurant with big tables and yummy Mexican food.  The service is friendly and the menu has something for everyone.  And cold beer!

data.title: Great food. Great prices. Friendly Staff.
data.text: Mariana and Chevo are great hosts. They have a menu that covers almost everyone's taste. I have been coming here for years and everything I have tried has ALWAYS been fresh and delicious. They have daily specials that are great discounts from off the main menu. I do recommend coming here, I have even brought my clients to lunch here. The reason for the 4 and not 5 stars is the chairs and tables are uncomfortable to sit in. Otherwise everything else is GREAT!! :-D

data.title: Really Good Mexican Food
data.text:
Two great things about chevo's. One, it’s just a couple of blocks away from the house, second they serve really good Mexican food. One of the best Mexican restaurants in Apple Valley.

We usually call in for a takeout order of burritos. I have the Carne Asada; the wife has chicken. On this trip we decided to eat in, then head over to the Off the Grid Brewery, just a few blocks away.

I had the Carne Asada tacos. Now, I have spent some time in Baja California and have eaten tacos from some places most American’s would just pass by. Some of those were the best tacos ever. Chevo's is as close to some of those great taco places as I have found in the US.

data.title: 😊
data.text: Since the other place I went to was closed I thought I would try them. Got the tacos and rice. Very good, hot and fresh. Home made shells. Been back a few time's. Very happy, keep up with the good food.

data.title: Excellent Food at a Low Price... depending on the day...
data.text: Chevo's is one of my favorite local restaurants.  I love their bean and cheese burritos.  Honestly, I like their re-fried beans better than any (including high end) Mexican restaurants.  They are fabulous!  The problem is inconsistency.  There are times that we go and the service is exceptional and the food is wonderful!  There are other times that the wait is excessively long and the food is cold or worse... microwaved.  There are times that there is a small amount of beans in my burrito and other times, when it's overflowing.  If the service and food were consistent this rating would be an excellent!  Please consider hiring more staff for weekends and other busy times.  Thanks for the wonderful food!  (Just an aside:  This is a small, family owned and operated business, so have that expectation.)

data.title: Great service and food at a reasonable price
data.text:
This is a great Mexican food restaurant, for breakfast, lunch or dinner! The salsa is fresh and delicious, the food is good portions and very tasty! 
The atmosphere isn't quite as cozy at it could be, but the food makes up for that, and they even have a drive through!!

data.title: Great lunch!
data.text: Met a friend for lunch (we went at 11:30) and he suggested shrimp tacos. They were great and the meal had rice & beans too. We were so happy to have gone early because this place was packed by the time we left! The service was friendly and fast. The chips and salsa really good too. I am going back for breakfast soon!

data.title: i dont understand why my friends love this place
data.text: extremely slow service, food was burnt, portion sizes were appropriate.  saying they had extremely slow service indicates that there was some service. NOT.

data.title: Great food & prices!
data.text: We love Chevo's, but some times it takes quite a while to get our food.  They tend to be very busy on Friday nights and weekends.  We try to go when it won't be busy or plan on waiting.  Great food and prices!  Our favorites: Albondigas soup and chicken tacos.

data.title: Great Mexican Food
data.text: The food is great here, i wished i was a bigger eater. i couldn't get enough.Staff were friendly and service was top class

data.title: Never again!! Life is too short !!
data.text: Went there once after hearing how good the food was..Well , we never got a chance to find out  we were in the drive through for 45 mins. and never made it too the window to order.. After the car behind us got fed up . we were able to escape. And went to Del Taco So much for that.!!!

data.title: Best Mexican food in the area!
data.text: We've been coming to Chevos for several years.  I found it when going to different restaurants trying to find authentic (street style) tacos.  Chevos tacos are amazing.  Actually, all of the food is great.  My family gets various items from tacos, to burritos, to shrimp skewers, to fish tacos.  We love it all!  We come here for just about every special occasion in our family!
